        <div>
          <h4> SMR Pressure-Point Massage</h4>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          {{!-- <img src="images/smr/pectoralis-minor-SMR.jpg"> --}}
          <img src="images/smr/SMR Pectoralis Minor.jpg">
          <img src="images/smr/theracane-pec.jpeg">
          <p class="card-title"> Pectoralis Minor SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Tennis/Lacrosse ball or Theracane Device </p>
          <p class="directions"> Apply circular rolling pressure by placing the ball between the pec and the shoulder. 
             Apply pressure using your bodyweight. This can be done laying face-down on the ground, or by leaning forward into a wall. </p>
        </div>  
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img class="trapezius" src="images/neck/Trapezius anatomy.jpeg">
          <img src="images/smr/SMR-Thoracic-spine.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Thoracic Spine & Lower Trapezius SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Foam-roller or Tennis balls </p>
          <p class="directions"> Keeping the arms crossed, roll over the device to massage the muscles along your spine - from your neck to mid-back. </p>
          <p class="directions"> For safety, avoid rolling out the lower-back as this has little benefits and can aggravate pre-existing problems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img src="images/smr/SMR Trapezius-Middle.jpg">
          <img src="images/smr/theracane-serratus-posterior-release-1.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Middle Trapezius SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Tennis/Lacrosse ball or Theracane Device </p>
          <p class="directions"> Place a ball between your back and a flat, solid wall. Position it just above one of your shoulder blades and lean back into it.</p>
          <p class="directions"> Roll the ball circularly, seeking out any sore points or muscular tension. </p>
          <p class="directions"> If you are using a Theracane, use the hook end to massage out the area just between the spine and shoulder blade. </p>
        </div>
        <div class="smr-card">
          <img class="trapezius" src="images/neck/upper-trap-acupressure.jpg">
          <p class="card-title"> Upper Trapezius SMR </p>
          <p class="directions"> Requires : Tennis/Lacrosse ball or Theracane Device </p>
          <p class="directions"> Feel for tension in the large muscle located between the base of your skull and shoulders. </p>
          <p class="directions"> Apply and hold pressure to the pair of points <i>centrally-located between your ear and base of your skull</i> (you will feel a small bump in the bone where the muscle attaches). 
             You can use a device, the thumbs, or the pointer/middle fingers.</p>
          <p class="directions"> Next, feel for tension in the points between the base of the neck and shoulder, just above the shoulder blade. Apply and hold pressure </p>
          <img src="images/smr/SMR Trapezius-Upper.png">
        </div>
